  "text": "14 To avoid the need to explore the radial nerve in the distal, plate length was selected so that distal of the plate would remain 8 cm above the lateral epicondyle. Despite this, temporary radial palsy complication was reported in 3 patients. [CITATION_1] In the current study, the radial nerve was routinely explored and protected. Although the main aim of this was not to cause any damage to the radial nerve, it also ensured that secondary exploration ",
